CM_TOOLS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The RCS utilities in this package have been tested on an Apollo Domain system,
and on SunOs systems.


Common options:

	* = lowest-level/not common
	+ = mapped into lower-level application (common)
	C = common option (with common meaning in different applications)
	_ = unimplemented

	A = all-directories (includes "." ones)
	L = follow links
	N = no-op
	O = output-redirection
	Q = quiet
	R = recur
	T = trace/log
	V = verbose
	X = extended path

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
         abcdefghijklm nopqrstuvwxyz  ABCDEFGHIJKLM NOPQRSTUVWXYZ  uses
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ci       ---*-*----*C* *--Q****-*---  ------------- *------------
co       ---*-*---*-C- --*Q**-*-*---  ------------- -------------
rcs      ***-*---*--C- **-Q-***-----  *----------*- *------*-----
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
baseline A----------** N--Q----V----  -----------L- ----R--------  checkin/out
checkin  -----+----+++ +--Q++++-----  -*-N--------- +------------  ci
checkout --*------_-+- --+Q++---+---  ------------- -------------  co
checkup  A-*?----*--T- -**Q*Q*-V-*--  ------------- -------------
copy     ---*----*--** N----*-*V----  ------------- -------------
link2rcs A*-***------* N--Q**--V----  ------------- -------------
permit   +*--+-------* N-*Q---*V----  ------------- -------------  rcs
rcsget   A--*--------- N--Q---------  -----------L- ----R-*------  checkout
rcsput   A+*N---+---T- -------------  ------------- ------*------  checkin,diff
vcs      ---*----*---- N--Q---*--X--  ------------- -------------  rcs

(Options of 'ded' are entirely different from the RCS tools)
